Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @sweet potato{300%grams} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional). Place onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and half the @dried thyme{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(grated) (or use a garlic press). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks. Zest the @lime{1} then halve and juice it. Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pot{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the scallion (keep a little aside for garnish). Season with salt and pepper and fry until soft and sweet, ~{1-2%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Add the pepper and fry for ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic, @garam masala{1%sachet} and remaining thyme. Fry for ~{30%seconds} and then add the @chopped tomatoes{1%pack}, @water{100%ml}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and the @coconut milk{180%ml}. Stir well.

Bring the soup to the boil. Allow it to simmer covered on low heat for ~{12-15%minutes}.

Add the kidney beans when the soup has about 5 mins left to cook. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Remove the soup from the heat. Stir in the roasted sweet potato. Add half of the lime juice.

Spoon the soup into #bowls{}. Garnish with lime zest and lime juice to taste. Finish with a sprinkling of scallion.